description: In ruby red Texas, a Democrat hasn’t been elected to a statewide position since 1994. But ahead of this year’s midterm election, a Senate race between an unflinching liberal and a religious conservative is unexpectedly close.
title: Beto O’Rourke, Ted Cruz and a (Possibly) Changing Texas
